on as a log-normal distribution and\nassuming a total Galactic contribution of 80 pc cm$^{-3}$, we find a median\nvalue of $\\mathrm{DM}_\\mathrm{host} =$ $84^{+69}_{-49}$ pc cm$^{-3}$,\ncomparable with values typically used in the literature. Proposed models for\nFRB progenitors should be consistent with the energetics and abundances of the\nfull FRB population predicted by our results. Finally, we infer the redshift\ndistribution of FRBs detected with CHIME, which will be tested with the\nlocalizations and redshifts enabled by the upcoming CHIME/FRB Outriggers\nproject.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 18:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 27 Apr 2023 19:45:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-01"}
